            "body": "> Many of the test changes defeat the entire point of these tests.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhich tests specifically? I don't see much reason to display options or buffer names with platform-specific slashes, so e.g. the changes `test/functional/options/defaults_spec.lua` look ok.\r\n\r\nBut some things like `fnamemodify()` may be required to return `\\` slashes, if they are used by plugins for \"normalization\". And 'shellslash' is an open question, but might be something we can temporarily break and see what the blast radius is.",
            "created_at": "2026-02-09T23:06:26Z",
